# IPO data sourcing policy

This app is an indirect competitor to InvestorGain, so we must NOT depend on any
single provider for facts. If our only source is wrong, we are wrong.

## Rules

- Never treat one website as the source of truth for hard facts. Hard facts are:
  price band (`priceMin`/`priceMax`), `lot`, `issueSize`, `freshIssue`, `ofs`,
  `faceValue`, and the timeline dates (`open`, `close`, `allotment`, `listing`).
- A hard fact may only be published (shown as a real value) once at least TWO
  independent sources agree. Otherwise it stays "pending verification". This gate
  lives in [scripts/reconcile.mjs](scripts/reconcile.mjs).
- Cross-verify against independent + official sources:
  Chittorgarh, NSE, BSE, and the SEBI RHP/DRHP. Adapters live in
  [scripts/sources/](scripts/sources/). Add new sources as adapters that export
  `fetchAll(...)` returning `{ name, fields, meta:{source,url,capturedAt} }`.
- GMP is the ONE exception: it may stay single-source (InvestorGain) because it
  is a grey-market estimate with no authoritative feed. Subscription figures and
  listing price are likewise operational, not gated.
- Every gated field must carry provenance in `ipo.verification[field]`
  (`verified` / `conflict` / `unverified` / `pending`) so the UI can show a trust
  badge and users can audit where a number came from.
- When adding a source, prefer official exchanges/regulators over aggregators.
  Source priority for tie-breaks: NSE/BSE > Chittorgarh > InvestorGain.
- Never silently overwrite a value from a single source. Only a >=2-source
  consensus may change an existing value.

## When researching a specific IPO by hand

Do your own research too: check at least two of Chittorgarh / NSE / BSE / the RHP
before stating a number, and note the sources. Do not restate InvestorGain alone.
